barking in distance]

645
00:33:10.841 --> 00:33:12.418
[Door closes]

646
00:33:13.144 --> 00:33:15.278
- [Indistinct conversations]
- [Sighs]

647
00:33:19.676 --> 00:33:20.861
[Door opens]

648
00:33:20.872 --> 00:33:23.396
Francis: Okay. and I'm still waiting
for those third-party subpoenas.

649
00:33:23.407 --> 00:33:24.927
Howard: Oh. great. Let me know. then.

650
00:33:24.938 --> 00:33:26.155
- Thanks. Francis.
- All right.

651
00:33:26.157 --> 00:33:28.857
Julie. what's up? From Chuck.

652
00:33:28.859 --> 00:33:30.859
It came via messenger...
the instructions say

653
00:33:30.861 --> 00:33:33.411
he wants you to read
it as soon as possible.

654
00:33:34.020 --> 00:33:35.322
[Door closes]

655
00:33:35.333 --> 00:33:36.575
Mm-hmm.

656
00:33:37.122 --> 00:33:38.867
Uh. here's what I need you to do.

657
00:33:38.869 --> 00:33:42.604
Call around. Find someplace
special for the retirement party.

658
00:33:42.606 --> 00:33:44.473
Something classy. old-school.

659
00:33:44.475 --> 00:33:46.175
Uh. La Posada. maybe.

660
00:33:46.177 --> 00:33:49.486
And a band. Something jazzy. Upbeat.

661
00:33:49.497 --> 00:33:50.653
Find what's available.

662
00:33:50.664 --> 00:33:52.051
- Let's set it up.
- Okay.

663
00:33:52.063 --> 00:33:53.747
[Envelope tearing]

664
00:33:54.119 --> 00:33:55.692
[Door opens]

665
00:33:56.946 --> 00:33:58.403
[Door closes]

666
00:34:06.032 --> 00:34:07.868
Goddamit. Chuck.

667
00:34:07.898 --> 00:34:09.235
[Door opens]

668
00:34:10.321 --> 00:34:12.446
You're suing Hamlin. Hamlin. McGill?

669
00:34:12.457 --> 00:34:14.164
Come on in. Howard.

670
00:34:15.141 --> 00:34:16.436
[Door slams]

671
00:34:16.447 --> 00:34:17.890
[Sizzling]

672
00:34:17.901 --> 00:34:19.547
You turned the lights on.

673
00:34:19.558 --> 00:34:23.078
I told you... I'm back to normal.

674
00:34:23.080 --> 00:34:26.560
And yes. I am suing HHM
for breach of contract.

675
00:34:26.571 --> 00:34:28.579
Do you have any idea what you're doing?

676
00:34:28.590 --> 00:34:30.352
[Sighs] I believe I do.

677
00:34:30.363 --> 00:34:32.321
I'm calling your bluff.

678
00:34:32.323 --> 00:34:35.091
This is my firm. I built it.

679
00:34:35.102 --> 00:34:38.560
Your father was working in a
two-room office when I joined him.

680
00:34:38.562 --> 00:34:41.568
And you I tutored for the bar exam.

681
00:34:41.579 --> 00:34:42.998
You're not kicking me out.

682
00:34:43.000 --> 00:34:45.334
If you can't "trust my
judgment." as you say.

683
00:34:45.336 --> 00:34:46.668
so be it.

684
00:34:46.670 --> 00:34:49.614
but you're gonna have
to pay me for my share.

685
00:34:49.625 --> 00:34:52.674
I believe it comes to around $8 million.

686
00:34:52.676 --> 00:34:55.297
We both know the firm
doesn't have the money.

687
00:34:56.649 --> 00:34:59.583
You'd rather tear down HHM than retire?

688
00:34:59.594 --> 00:35:02.509
You think I'm trouble
now? As your partner?

689
00:35:02.520 --> 00:35:04.610
Imagine me as your enemy.

690
00:35:07.511 --> 00:35:09.031
[Immersion blender whirring]

691
00:35:09.042 --> 00:35:10.375
Chuck...

692
00:35:11.237 --> 00:35:12.761
the damage that you're going to do...

693
00:35:12.763 --> 00:35:14.753
- [Whirring stops]
- If you'd like to discuss this further.

694
00:35:14.764 --> 00:35:16.976
we can... in court.

695
00:35:16.987 --> 00:35:18.567
Until then...

696
00:35:19.417 --> 00:35:21.937
what else is there to say?

697
00:35:22.681 --> 00:35:25.148
[Whirring continues]

698
00:35:30.564 --> 00:35:32.030
[Door opens]

699
00:35:32.042 --> 00:35:33.711
[Door slams]

700
00:35:33.713 --> 00:35:35.464
[Whirring stops]

701
00:35:35.475 --> 00:35:37.222
[Sizzling]

702
00:35:37.901 --> 00:35:40.383
[Sniffles. clears throat]

703
00:35:40.394 --> 00:35:42.424
[Sighs] Blue pot. Red wine.

704
00:35:42.426 --> 00:35:44.226
Black burner.

705
00:35:44.228 --> 00:35:46.261
Blue pot. Red wine.

706
00:35:46.878 --> 00:35:49.995
Black burner. Blue pot.
Red wine. Black burner.

707
00:35:51.159 --> 00:35:52.729
[Clears throat]

708
00:35:53.604 --> 00:35:54.972
[Sighing]

709
00:35:56.988 --> 00:36:00.651
[Air hissing]

710
00:36:08.005 --> 00:36:10.072
[Liquid sloshing]

711
00:36:14.425 --> 00:36:15.891
[Ball taps]

712
00:36:20.616 --> 00:36:22.249
[Liquid sloshing]

713
00:36:36.328 --> 00:36:38.668
[Balls clattering]

714
00:36:38.679 --> 00:36:40.379
Jimmy: I got hot hands.

715
00:36:40.381 --> 00:36:43.124
I got hot hands! I know
this is gonna be the one!

716
00:36:43.135 --> 00:36:45.518
B-9!

717
00:36:45.566 --> 00:36:49.992
Let's hope that biopsy comes back "B-9."

718
00:36:50.003 --> 00:36:51.585
B-9.

719
00:36:52.218 --> 00:36:53.893
[Door opens]

720
00:36:54.976 --> 00:36:57.156
Okay... what's next?

721
00:36:57.167 --> 00:36:58.500
[Air hisses]

722
00:36:58.511 --> 00:37:00.710
We got... I-29.

723
00:37:00.721 --> 00:37:03.101
I remember when I was 29.

724
00:37:03.112 --> 00:37:05.346
Bet you do. too.

725
00:37:05.357 --> 00:37:07.688
I-29.

726
00:37:13.374 --> 00:37:16.968
Here comes O-62.

727
00:37:17.945 --> 00:37:19.652
Oh. my God.

728
00:37:19.654 --> 00:37:21.999
Have I called 62 of
these already? [Chuckling]

729
00:37:22.010 --> 00:37:25.124
It feels like it. O-62.

730
00:37:26.101 --> 00:37:28.335
Here we have B-2.

731
00:37:28.346 --> 00:37:29.781
B-2.

732
00:37:29.792 --> 00:37:32.498
Well. tonight is all bingo.

733
00:37:32.500 --> 00:37:33.843
Here it comes.

734
00:37:33.854 --> 00:37:36.502
O-70. Anyone? O-70.

735
00:37:37.124 --> 00:37:39.226
All right. No takers.

736
00:37:39.237 --> 00:37:40.781
Boom!

737
00:37:41.343 --> 00:37:42.942
G-55.

738
00:37:42.944 --> 00:37:44.344
G-55.

739
00:37:44.346 --> 00:37:46.012
Oh. my God! Bingo!

740
00:37:46.014 --> 00:37:47.351
- I got bingo!
- [Applause]

741
00:37:47.362 --> 00:37:49.582
Big Paul. bring it up.

742
00:37:49.584 --> 00:37:51.254
Kelly. take a look.

743
00:37:51.265 --> 00:37:53.734
- [Applause continues]
- We may have a winner.

744
00:37:54.316 --> 00:37:57.171
Kelly. tell me... have we got it?

745
00:37:57.182 --> 00:37:58.478
We have a bingo!

746
00:37:58.489 --> 00:38:00.956
Paul. step up to the winner's circle.

747
00:38:00.967 --> 00:38:02.335
Let's hear it for him!

748
00:38:02.346 --> 00:38:04.579
Let's give him a big round of applause!

749
00:38:04.590 --> 00:38:06.857
[Applause]

750
00:38:06.868 --> 00:38:09.202
Okay. New game. new cards.

751
00:38:09.204 --> 00:38:10.703
Here they come.

752
00:38:10.705 --> 00:38:13.085
Get yourself some new cards. New cards.

753
00:38:13.132 --> 00:38:14.741
[Microphone feedback]

754
00:38:14.743 --> 00:38:17.333
The helpers have them.
You can have one. two.

755
00:38:17.344 --> 00:38:19.648
You can have up to four. as you know.

756
00:38:20.046 --> 00:38:22.840
Here's a lucky blue one for you.

757
00:38:22.851 --> 00:38:26.351
All right. Take your cards
so we can start a new game.

758
00:38:26.353 --> 00:38:29.320
There you go. Add that to your stack.

759
00:38:30.453 --> 00:38:31.990
All right. Get your cards.

760
00:38:31.992 --> 00:38:34.543
Hey. Irene. you feeling lucky today?

761
00:38:34.554 --> 00:38:36.161
I-I guess so.

762
00:38:36.163 --> 00:38:38.897
[Chuckling] All right.
Well. here's one on me...

763
00:38:38.899 --> 00:38:40.365
just for you.

764
00:38:41.171 --> 00:38:46.265
All right. I sold my
soul for B-I-N-G-and-O!

765
00:38:46.773 --> 00:38:49.304
Let's clear the table.

766
00:38:49.315 --> 00:38:51.929
[Indistinct conversations]

767
00:38:53.354 --> 00:38:54.992
[Sniffles]

768
00:39:04.166 --> 00:39:08.293
♪ ♪

769
00:39:08.830 --> 00:39:10.315
Load it up.

770
00:39:10.885 --> 00:39:14.098
[Balls clattering]

771
00:39:14.100 --> 00:39:16.067
♪ ♪

772
00:39:16.807 --> 00:39:18.536
Locked and loaded.

773
00:39:18.538 --> 00:39:20.174
[Cabinet door closes]

774
00:39:20.185 --> 00:39:21.698
[Sighs]

775
00:39:25.611 --> 00:39:27.630
Here comes a new game.

776
00:39:27.641 --> 00:39:28.874
[Switch clicks]

777
00:39:28.885 --> 00:39:32.383
♪ ♪

778
00:39:32.385 --> 00:39:34.886
First number up...

779
00:39:34.888 --> 00:39:36.866
♪ ♪

780
00:39:36.877 --> 00:39:39.482
it's N-31.

781
00:39:39.493 --> 00:39:41.033
"N" for "Nancy."

782
00:39:41.044 --> 00:39:44.257
31 for the number of times
she told me to take a hike.

783
00:39:44.268 --> 00:39:47.205
N-31.

784
00:39:47.216 --> 00:39:49.429
♪ ♪

785
00:39:49.440 --> 00:39:51.218
G-48.

786
00:39:51.229 --> 00:39:53.682
"G" for the Greatest Generation.

787
00:39:53.693 --> 00:39:56.808
48 for "Dewey Defeats Truman."

788
00:39:56.810 --> 00:40:00.343
Here's I-25... the big "I."

789
00:40:00.354 --> 00:40:01.897
I-25.

790
00:40:01.947 --> 00:40:05.817
It's B-12. like the vitamin.

791
00:40:05.819 --> 00:40:09.625
♪ ♪

792
00:40:13.870 --> 00:40:15.460
O-67!

793
00:40:15.462 --> 00:40:18.605
Anybody? I got a good
feeling about this.

794
00:40:18.616 --> 00:40:21.206
O-67!

795
00:40:23.050 --> 00:40:26.430
I-I-I think... Bingo!

796
00:40:26.441 --> 00:40:27.705
Who is that?

797
00:40:27.707 --> 00:40:29.277
Come on up.

798
00:40:30.034 --> 00:40:34.234
Irene! Irene. come on up here. dear.

799
00:40:34.245 --> 00:40:36.953
Bring it up to Kelly. Let's take a look.

800
00:40:36.964 --> 00:40:39.217
Kelly has to check your card.

801
00:40:39.219 --> 00:40:41.042
[Balls clattering]

802
00:40:41.053 --> 00:40:43.153
Here she comes.

803
00:40:43.164 --> 00:40:46.917
♪ ♪

804
00:40:47.706 --> 00:40:49.550
Could be...

805
00:40:50.339 --> 00:40:52.196
♪ ♪

806
00:40:52.198 --> 00:40:54.499
Oh. my goodness.

807
00:40:54.501 --> 00:40:58.469
It is a bingo for Irene!

808
00:40:58.471 --> 00:41:00.672
Let's hear it for Irene Landry!

809
00:41:00.674 --> 00:41:02.534
[Scattered applause]

810
00:41:02.550 --> 00:41:05.738
Give it up for the big
winner. Irene Landry!

811
00:41:05.749 --> 00:41:07.378
[Scattered applause continues]

812
00:41:07.380 --> 00:41:09.660
Fastest bingo of the night!

813
00:41:09.671 --> 00:41:12.150
Come on. Let's hear it for Irene.

814
00:41:12.152 --> 00:41:13.436
- Oh!
- [Thumps]

815
00:41:14.038 --> 00:41:15.086
[Crying]

816
00:41:15.088 --> 00:41:16.288
Irene...

817
00:41:16.299 --> 00:41:17.347
- where ya goin'?
- [Door opens]

818
00:41:17.358 --> 00:41:19.554
Hey. you know what? Take over.

819
00:41:21.100 --> 00:41:23.328
Okay. Time for a new game.

820
00:41:23.330 --> 00:41:26.214
Uh. let's get some
cards out for everyone.

821
00:41:26.225 --> 00:41:27.593
[Crying]

822
00:41:27.604 --> 00:41:29.093
[Door opens]

823
00:41:31.749 --> 00:41:33.087
[Chuckling] Hey.

824
00:41:33.098 --> 00:41:35.170
What's going on? You okay?

825
00:41:35.181 --> 00:41:36.981
[Crying]

826
00:41:37.116 --> 00:41:39.183
Aww. Don't do that.

827
00:41:39.194 --> 00:41:42.116
Your mascara's gonna run all over.

828
00:41:42.127 --> 00:41:44.347
[Crying continues]

829
00:41:44.358 --> 00:41:46.551
Irene. come on.

830
00:41:46.553 --> 00:41:48.311
What's wrong?

831
00:41:48.722 --> 00:41:50.188
[Sniffles]

832
00:41:50.190 --> 00:41:52.811
They've all turned on me.

833
00:41:52.822 --> 00:41:54.132
[Crying]

834
00:41:54.143 --> 00:41:55.743
Who has?

835
00:41:56.196 --> 00:41:57.894
My friends!

836
00:41:57.931 --> 00:42:01.105
Helen. Rose. Myrtle.

837
00:42:01.116 --> 00:42:03.433
All of them.

838
00:42:03.444 --> 00:42:05.894
What? No!

839
00:42:05.905 --> 00:42:07.913
Yes!

840
00:42:07.929 --> 00:42:09.207
[Sniffles]

841
00:42:09.209 --> 00:42:11.561
They're so cold.

842
00:42:12.702 --> 00:42:16.496
When I walk past them.
they stop talking.

843
00:42:16.498 --> 00:42:18.374
I-I-I hear them whispering

844
00:42:18.385 --> 00:42:21.219
when... when they think I'm not there.

845
00:42:21.221 --> 00:42:23.819
It's just so...

846
00:42:23.990 --> 00:42:25.543
- It's so cruel.
- Mnh.

847
00:42:25.554 --> 00:42:27.725
And I don't even know why.

848
00:42:28.304 --> 00:42:30.757
[Sighs]

849
00:42:32.710 --> 00:42:34.999
I think. uh...

850
00:42:35.001 --> 00:42:37.101
maybe I do.

851
00:42:38.910 --> 00:42:40.775
- You do?
- [Sighs]

852
00:42:42.275 --> 00:42:44.242
[Sighs]

853
00:42:44.253 --> 00:42:46.828
Could it be the settlement?

854
00:42:46.839 --> 00:42:49.523
I mean. maybe they... [Inhales sharply]

855
00:42:49.534 --> 00:42:51.906
want the money.

856
00:42:51.917 --> 00:42:55.437
you know. to improve their lives?

857
00:42:55.448 --> 00:42:58.623
I had no idea any of them needed money.

858
00:42:58.625 --> 00:43:00.825
No one said anything to me.

859
00:43:00.827 --> 00:43:03.327
Well. maybe it's not
about the money itself.

860
00:43:03.329 --> 00:43:07.799
I mean... hello... who
wouldn't want more money?

861
00:43:07.801 --> 00:43:10.370
I mean. maybe it's the idea

862
00:43:10.381 --> 00:43:15.526
that they don't think you're
considering them. you know?

863
00:43:16.183 --> 00:43:18.309
Thinking of their needs?

864
00:43:18.311 --> 00:43:20.712
I-I-I didn't know.

865
00:43:20.714 --> 00:43:24.042
I don't want to hurt
them. They're my friends.

866
00:43:24.053 --> 00:43:25.919
[Breathing heavily]

867
00:43:26.987 --> 00:43:29.454
I wish we never even
started this lawsuit.

868
00:43:29.456 --> 00:43:32.539
I just want everything
to go back the way it was.

869
00:43:32.550 --> 00:43:34.826
[Breathing heavily]

870
00:43:35.550 --> 00:43:38.245
What should I do?

871
00:43:38.941 --> 00:43:41.480
What would you do?

872
00:43:43.636 --> 00:43:47.144
I mean. you know I'm
not a lawyer right now.

873
00:43:47.894 --> 00:43:49.674
Please?

874
00:43:51.135 --> 00:43:53.206
Should I settle?

875
00:43:54.823 --> 00:43:56.647
[Sighs]

876
00:43:57.542 --> 00:43:59.317
Irene...

877
00:44:01.331 --> 00:44:02.724
[Sighs]

878
00:44:02.735 --> 00:44:04.847
you listen to your heart.

879
00:44:17.001 --> 00:44:18.903
Uh. time?

880
00:44:18.905 --> 00:44:20.171
Two hours out.

881
00:44:20.173 --> 00:44:21.706
When did I say I was gonna leave?

882
00:44:21.708 --> 00:44:23.374
20 minutes ago.

883
00:44:24.111 --> 00:44:26.638
Uh. can I have some more coffee. please?

884
00:44:26.649 --> 00:44:28.462
Coming.

885
00:44:33.453 --> 00:44:36.445
Uh. I'm missing a survey
history in this one.

886
00:44:36.456 --> 00:44:38.984
- On it. Sorry about that.
- [Sighs]

887
00:44:38.995 --> 00:44:40.531
- [Coffee pouring]
- Not a problem.

888
00:44:40.542 --> 00:44:42.226
- [Door opens]
- Jimmy: Hey!

889
00:44:42.228 --> 00:44:44.729
Who's ready to have her life changed?

890
00:44:44.731 --> 00:44:46.264
Kim. did you hear me?

891
00:44:46.266 --> 00:44:48.332
Yep. Heard you. Life changed.

892
00:44:48.343 --> 00:44:52.136
[Chuckles] Stop your work.
both of you. for a sec.

893
00:44:52.138 --> 00:44:53.805
I-I got big. big news.

894
00:44:53.807 --> 00:44:55.640
Can you just tell us later. Jimmy?

895
00:44:55.642 --> 00:44:58.391
- I'm so late. it's not even funny.
- Mesa Verde can wait.

896
00:44:58.402 --> 00:45:01.245
- Look. I got Zafiro.
- It's not Mesa Verde.

897
00:45:01.247 --> 00:45:03.614
It's a new client. and if I mess
this up. it's a former client.

898
00:45:03.616 --> 00:45:05.716
I thought Mesa Verde
was your one and only.

899
00:45:05.718 --> 00:45:07.618
You know. it's go...
Ji... uh. I'm sorry.

900
00:45:07.629 --> 00:45:09.644
Jimmy. can I just explain
all this to you later? I'm...

901
00:45:09.655 --> 00:45:11.863
Sandpiper is settling.

902
00:45:12.492 --> 00:45:14.813
- What?
- [Chuckling] Yeah.

903
00:45:14.824 --> 00:45:16.456
For a bundle.

904
00:45:17.355 --> 00:45:19.163
But th-they can't be settling.

905
00:45:19.165 --> 00:45:21.165
[Chuckling] Class actions
don't move that fast.

906
00:45:21.167 --> 00:45:23.401
Don't get bogged down in the details!

907
00:45:23.426 --> 00:45:26.144
Trust me... they're settling!

908
00:45:27.711 --> 00:45:28.977
- Wow. that...
- [Both chuckle]

909
00:45:28.988 --> 00:45:30.756
- Yeah. Yeah!
- That's great. then.

910
00:45:30.767 --> 00:45:32.610
So. hey. let's celebrate.

911
00:45:32.612 --> 00:45:34.139
I can tell that you...

912
00:45:34.150 --> 00:45:36.447
pulled another
all-nighter here. you know?

913
00:45:36.449 --> 00:45:38.983
You... you got to stop
and smell the roses.

914
00:45:38.985 --> 00:45:41.986
Hey. who's got two
thumbs. a bottle of Zafiro.

915
00:45:41.988 --> 00:45:43.920
and 20% of the common fund?!

916
00:45:43.931 --> 00:45:45.122
- Huh?
- This guy!

917
00:45:45.124 --> 00:45:47.592
I know... you do. Uh. I
am happy for you. Jimmy.

918
00:45:47.594 --> 00:45:48.926
Be happy for us!

919
00:45:48.928 --> 00:45:51.240
This is the solution to everything.

920
00:45:51.251 --> 00:45:52.775
Okay. Francesca. could you
just put these all in my car?

921
00:45:52.786 --> 00:45:54.314
Kim.

922
00:45:54.325 --> 00:45:55.584
Yeah. Jimmy. I gotta go.

923
00:45:55.595 --> 00:45:57.490
Gimme five goddamn minutes.

924
00:45:57.501 --> 00:45:59.251
- I don't have five minutes.
- But you're already late.

925
00:45:59.262 --> 00:46:02.006
What's five more minutes?
So drive 60 instead of 55.

926
00:46:02.008 --> 00:46:03.619
- [Chuckling] Jimmy!
- What?

927
00:46:03.630 --> 00:46:05.129
- [Door opens]
- You're not hearing me.

928
00:46:05.140 --> 00:46:06.978
Our troubles are over! Come on!

929
00:46:06.980 --> 00:46:08.701
Jimmy. I'm leaving now.

930
00:46:08.712 --> 00:46:09.981
I'll be back in a few hours.

931
00:46:09.992 --> 00:46:11.181
Think of all the things
you want to say to me.

932
00:46:11.192 --> 00:46:12.808
and just say them to me later. okay?

933
00:46:12.819 --> 00:46:14.197
Bye.

934
00:46:14.208 --> 00:46:15.569
[Door closes]

935
00:46:20.826 --> 00:46:22.373
[Door opens]

936
00:46:24.428 --> 00:46:25.733
[Door closes]

937
00:46:25.744 --> 00:46:27.848
You. Shots.

938
00:46:27.882 --> 00:46:30.266
- Uh. I...
- Shots.

939
00:46:30.277 --> 00:46:32.143
We're celebrating.

940
00:46:38.117 --> 00:46:40.311
- Cheers.
- [Glasses clink]

941
00:46:41.680 --> 00:46:43.567
[Slurps]

942
00:46:43.578 --> 00:46:44.859
Smooth.

943
00:46:44.870 --> 00:46:46.517
[Exhales sharply]

944
00:46:46.519 --> 00:46:48.052
[Tapping counter]

945
00:46:48.054 --> 00:46:49.469
Yeah.

946
00:46:54.023 --> 00:46:57.995
Under the terms we're offering.
you get a substantial payment

947
00:46:57.997 --> 00:47:01.286
without any impact to your property
via drilling and extraction.

948
00:47:01.297 --> 00:47:02.667
And rather than waiting years to close.

949
00:47:02.669 --> 00:47:06.348
Mr. Gatwood is offering cash
on the barrel. right now.

950
00:47:06.359 --> 00:47:09.450
Given the cost of overhead. liabilities.

951
00:47:09.461 --> 00:47:11.742
and other burdens Mr. Gatwood assumes.

952
00:47:11.744 --> 00:47:14.305
we believe this offer is more than fair.

953
00:47:14.316 --> 00:47:15.912
We believe...

954
00:47:16.399 --> 00:47:19.914
we believe this offer is more than fair.

955
00:47:33.199 --> 00:47:34.853
[Gasps]

956
00:47:34.864 --> 00:47:38.392
[Air rushing]

957
00:47:39.009 --> 00:47:42.400
[Breathing heavily]

958
00:47:48.299 --> 00:47:50.619
[Door creaks]

959
00:47:56.723 --> 00:48:00.057
[Whimpers]

960
00:48:01.267 --> 00:48:02.952
Aah!

961
00:48:02.963 --> 00:48:07.365
[Breathing shakily]

962
00:48:24.350 --> 00:48:27.718
[Wind whistling]

963
00:48:41.214 --> 00:48:44.953
